import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], errors='ignore')
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], errors='ignore')
    
    sns.lineplot(x='budgetYear', y='value', data=data, label='Budget')
    sns.lineplot(x='forecastYear', y='value', data=data, label='Forecast')
    
    plt.title('What is the trend of budget and forecast values over time?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], errors='ignore')
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], errors='ignore')
    
    avg_budget = data.groupby('budgetYear')['value'].mean().reset_index()
    avg_forecast = data.groupby('forecastYear')['value'].mean().reset_index()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    sns.barplot(x='budgetYear', y='value', data=avg_budget, label='Budget')
    sns.barplot(x='forecastYear', y='value', data=avg_forecast, label='Forecast')
    
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Average Value')
    plt.title('What is the average budget and forecast value per year?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
